//
//   Where possible the ID name is the AutoCAD command name.
//   An ID is no more than 12 characters long.
//   Long command names are truncated (not abbreviated) to fit.
//   An ID names for a command opion appends the option to the command name:
//
//       Example:  the ID for Zoom Window is ID_ZoomWin
//
//   IDs are listed in alphabetical order.
//   Helps strings end with a colon, two spaces and the name of the command.
//

***HELPSTRINGS
ID_3darray   [Creates a three-dimensional array:  3darray]
ID_3dface    [Creates a three-dimensional face:  3dface]
ID_3dmesh    [Creates a free-form polygon mesh:  3dmesh]
ID_3dpoly    [Creates a polyline of straight line segments in three-dimensional space:  3dpoly]
ID_3dsin     [Imports a 3D Studio file:  3dsin]
ID_3dsurface [Creates three-dimensional surface objects using a dialog box]
ID_About     [Displays information about AutoCAD:  about]
ID_Acisin    [Imports an ACIS file:  acisin]
ID_Ai_box    [Creates a three-dimensional box polygon mesh:  ai_box]
ID_Ai_cone   [Creates a cone-shaped polygon mesh:  ai_cone]
ID_Ai_dish   [Creates the lower half of a spherical polygon mesh:  ai_dish]
ID_Ai_dome   [Creates the upper half of a spherical polygon mesh:  ai_dome]
ID_Ai_fms    [Switches to floating model space:  ai_fms]
ID_Ai_molc   [Makes the layer of a selected object the current layer: ai_molc]
ID_Ai_propch [Runs DDMODIFY if a single object is selected, otherwise runs DDCHPROP:  ai_propchk]
ID_Ai_pspace [Switches to paper space:  ai_pspace]
ID_Ai_pyrami [Creates a pyramid or a tetrahedron:  ai_pyramid]
ID_Ai_sphere [Creates a spherical polygon mesh:  ai_sphere]
ID_Ai_tiledv [Displays layout options for tiled viewports]
ID_Ai_torus  [Creates a toroidal polygon mesh that is parallel to the XY plane of the current UCS:  ai_torus]
ID_Ai_wedge  [Creates a right-angle wedge-shaped polygon mesh with the sloped face tapering along the X axis:  ai_wedge]
ID_Align     [Moves and rotates objects to align with other objects:  align]
ID_Appload   [Loads AutoLISP, ADS, and ARX applications:  appload]
ID_Arc       [Creates an arc:  arc]
ID_Arc3point [Creates an arc using three points:  arc]
ID_ArcCeStAn [Creates an arc using the center, start point, and included angle:  arc]
ID_ArcCeStEn [Creates an arc using the center, start point, and endpoint:  arc]
ID_ArcCeStLe [Creates an arc using the center, start point, and length of chord:  arc]
ID_ArcContin [Creates an arc tangent to the last line or arc drawn:  arc]
ID_ArcStCeAn [Creates an arc using the start point, center, and included angle:  arc]
ID_ArcStCeEn [Creates an arc using the start point, center, and endpoint:  arc]
ID_ArcStCeLe [Creates an arc using the start point, center, and length of chord:  arc]
ID_ArcStEnAg [Creates an arc using the start point, endpoint, and included angle:  arc]
ID_ArcStEnDi [Creates an arc using the start point, endpoint, and starting direction:  arc]
ID_ArcStEnRa [Creates an arc using the start point, endpoint, and radius:  arc]
ID_Area      [Calculates the area and perimeter of objects or of defined areas:  area]
ID_Array     [Creates multiple copies of objects in a pattern:  array]
ID_Aseadmin  [Performs administrative functions for external database commands:  aseadmin]
ID_Aseexport [Exports link information for selected objects:  aseexport]
ID_Aselinks  [Manages links between objects and an external database:  aselinks]
ID_Aserows   [Displays and edits table data, and creates links and selection sets:  aserows]
ID_Aseselect [Creates a selection set from rows linked to textual selection sets and graphic selection sets:  aseselect]
ID_Asesqled  [Executes Structured Query Language (SQL) statements:  asesqled]
ID_AttdispNo [Visible attributes are displayed; invisible attributes are not displayed:  attdisp]
ID_AttdispOf [Makes all attributes invisible:  attdisp]
ID_AttdispOn [Makes all attributes visible:  attdisp]
ID_Attedit   [Changes attribute information independent of its block definition:  attedit]
ID_Audit     [Evaluates the integrity of a drawing:  audit]
ID_Backgroun [Sets the rendering background:  background]
ID_Base      [Sets the insertion base point for the current drawing:  base]
ID_Bhatch    [Fills an enclosed area with a hatch pattern:  bhatch]
ID_Bmake     [Defines a block using a dialog box:  bmake]
ID_Boundary  [Creates a region or a polyline from an enclosed area:  boundary]
ID_Box       [Creates a three-dimensional solid box:  box]
ID_Break     [Erases parts of objects or splits an object in two:  break]
ID_Browser   [Launches the default Web browser defined in your system’s registry:  browser]
ID_Chamfer   [Bevels the edges of objects:  chamfer]
ID_Circle    [Creates a circle:  circle]
ID_Circle2pt [Creates a circle using two endpoints of the diameter:  circle]
ID_Circle3pt [Creates a circle using three points on the circumference:  circle]
ID_CircleDia [Creates a circle using a specified diameter:  circle]
ID_CircleRad [Creates a circle using a specified radius:  circle]
ID_CircleTTR [Creates a circle tangent to two objects with a specified radius:  circle]
ID_CircleTTT [Creates a circle tangent to three objects:  circle]
ID_Cone      [Creates a three-dimensional solid cone:  cone]
ID_Config    [Displays the Preferences dialog box with Printer tab in front:  config]
ID_Copy      [Duplicates objects:  copy]
ID_Copyclip  [Copies objects to the Clipboard:  copyclip]
ID_Copylink  [Copies the current view to the Clipboard for linking to other OLE applications:  copylink]
ID_CtrlColor [Sets the default color for new objects and edits the color of existing objects]
ID_CtrlLayer [Sets the default layer for new objects, edits the layer of existing objects, and switches between layer properties]
ID_CtrlLinet [Sets the default linetype for new objects and edits the linetype of existing objects]
ID_Cutclip   [Copies objects to the Clipboard and erases the objects from the drawing:  cutclip]
ID_Cylinder  [Creates a three-dimensional solid cylinder:  cylinder]
ID_Ddattdef  [Creates an attribute definition:  ddattdef]
ID_Ddatte    [Edits the variable attributes of a block:  ddatte]
ID_Ddcolor   [Sets the color for new objects:  ddcolor]
ID_Ddedit    [Edits text and attribute definitions:  ddedit]
ID_Ddgrips   [Turns on grips and sets their color:  ddgrips]
ID_Ddim      [Creates and modifies dimension styles:  ddim]
ID_Ddinsert  [Inserts a block or another drawing:  ddinsert]
ID_Ddmodify  [Controls properties of existing objects:  ddmodify]
ID_Ddptype   [Specifies the display style and size of point objects:  ddptype]
ID_Ddrename  [Changes the names of named objects:  ddrename]
ID_Ddrmodes  [Sets drawing aids:  ddrmodes]
ID_Ddselect  [Sets object selection modes:  ddselect]
ID_Dducs     [Manages defined user coordinate systems:  dducs]
ID_Dducsp    [Selects a preset user coordinate system:  dducsp]
ID_Ddunits   [Controls coordinate and angle display formats and determines precision:  ddunits]
ID_Ddview    [Creates and restores views:  ddview]
ID_Ddvpoint  [Sets the three-dimensional viewing direction:  ddvpoint]
ID_Dimaligne [Creates an aligned linear dimension:  dimaligned]
ID_Dimangula [Creates an angular dimension:  dimangular]
ID_Dimbaseli [Continues a linear, angular, or ordinate dimension from the baseline of the previous or selected dimension:  dimbaseline]
ID_Dimcenter [Creates the center mark or the center lines of circles and arcs:  dimcenter]
ID_Dimcontin [Continues a linear, angular, or ordinate dimension from the second extension line of the previous or a selected dimension:  dimcontinue]
ID_Dimdiamet [Creates diameter dimensions for circles and arcs:  dimdiameter]
ID_Dimedit   [Edits dimensions:  dimedit]
ID_Dimlinear [Creates linear dimensions:  dimlinear]
ID_Dimordina [Creates ordinate point dimensions:  dimordinate]
ID_Dimoverri [Overrides dimension system variables:  dimoverride]
ID_Dimradius [Creates radial dimensions for circles and arcs:  dimradius]
ID_DimstyleA [Updates the dimension objects so they use the current dimensioning system variables settings:  dimstyle]
ID_Dimtedit  [Moves and rotates dimension text:  dimtedit]
ID_DimteditA [Rotates dimension text to an angle:  dimtedit]
ID_DimteditC [Centers dimension text:  dimtedit]
ID_DimteditH [Moves dimension text back to its default position:  dimtedit]
ID_DimteditL [Left justifies dimension text:  dimtedit]
ID_DimteditR [Right justifies dimension text:  dimtedit]
ID_DimUpdate [Updates the style of a dimension:  dim]
ID_Dist      [Measures the distance and angle between two points:  dist]
ID_Divide    [Places evenly spaced point objects or blocks along the length or perimeter of an object:  divide]
ID_Donut     [Draws filled circles and rings:  donut]
ID_DrawordeA [Forces selected objects to be displayed in front of a reference object:  draworder]
ID_DrawordeB [Forces selected objects to be displayed behind all other objects:  draworder]
ID_DrawordeF [Forces selected objects to be displayed in front of all other objects:  draworder]
ID_Draworder [Changes the display order of images and other objects:  draworder]
ID_DrawordeU [Forces selected objects to be displayed behind a reference object:  draworder]
ID_Dsviewer  [Opens the Aerial View window:  dsviewer]
ID_Dtext     [Displays text on screen as it is entered:  dtext]
ID_Dview     [Defines a parallel projection or perspective view:  dview]
ID_Dxbin     [Imports specially coded binary files:  dxbin]
ID_Dxfin     [Imports a drawing interchange file:  dxfin]
ID_Edge      [Changes the visibility of three-dimensional face edges:  edge]
ID_Edgesurf  [Creates a three-dimensional polygon mesh:  edgesurf]
ID_Ellipse   [Creates an ellipse or an elliptical arc:  ellipse]
ID_EllipseAx [Creates an ellipse using a specified axis:  ellipse]
ID_EllipseCe [Creates an ellipse using the center:  ellipse]
ID_EllipseAr [Creates an elliptical arc:  ellipse]
ID_Enter     [Presses the Enter key]
ID_Erase     [Removes objects from a drawing:  erase]
ID_Explode   [Breaks a compound object into its component objects:  explode]
ID_Export    [Saves objects to other file formats:  export]
ID_Extend    [Extends an object to meet another object:  extend]
ID_Extrude   [Creates unique solid primitives by extruding existing two-dimensional objects:  extrude]
ID_Fillet    [Rounds and fillets the edges of objects:  fillet]
ID_Fog       [Controls the fogging of a rendering:  fog]
ID_From      [Snaps to a temporary reference point:  from]
ID_GotoURL   [Loads the Web browser and searches for the location embedded in the selected object:  geturl]
ID_GripBase  [Sets the reference point]
ID_GripCopy  [Duplicates objects]
ID_GripExit  [Cancels grip edit mode and returns to the command line]
ID_GripMirro [Creates a mirror image copy of objects]
ID_GripMove  [Displaces objects a specified distance in a specified direction]
ID_GripRefer [Sets the reference point]
ID_GripRotat [Moves objects about a base point]
ID_GripScale [Enlarges or reduces selected objects equally in the X, Y, and Z directions]
ID_GripStret [Moves or stretches objects]
